      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "t_start": 23,
      "estimated_duration_s": 11,
      "narration_text": "Classically, if kinetic energy is zero inside the barrier, there is no motion. The particle cannot be there. The wavefunction must be zero. But it isn't.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "hold"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 8.83,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T12:34:14"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "t_start": 34,
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "narration_text": "Inside a forbidden region, Schrödinger's equation gives ψ'' = κ²ψ — a real exponential, not an oscillation. The wavefunction decays, but it does not reach zero.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "GRAPHIC",
        "source": "own",
        "motion": "accumulate"
      },
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.67,
